{\sname} was identified by citizen scientists Tom Bickle, Martin Kabatnik, and Austin Rothermich in multi-epoch unWISE images \citep{2014AJ....147..108L,2018AJ....156...69M,2019ApJS..240...30S} 
%served through the Wiseview ``flip book'' \citep{2018ascl.soft06004C} 
on the BYW citizen science portal.\footnote{{\url{http://www.backyardworlds.org}.}} Its $W2$ magnitude and $J-W2$ color (Table~\ref{tab:source}) 
%= 1.51$\pm$0.07 color based on data from the UKIRT Hemisphere Survey (UHS; Dye et al.\ 2018) and the the CatWISE catalog (Meisner et al.\ 2021) 
suggest an early-type L dwarf at an estimated distance of $\approx$100~pc \citep{2021ApJS..253....7K}.

